'''Yoshuku Performing Arts''' (予祝芸能) refers to [[traditional performing arts]] viewed from the perspective of [[faith]], including celebratory [[performing arts]] such as [[Manzai]] and [[Harukoma]], which commemorate the New Year, as well as [[Ta-asobi]] and [[Onda]] rituals, where agricultural activities are enacted in advance to pray for a successful rice harvest.

The practice involves preemptively celebrating to pray for the realization of those blessings, rooted in the belief and thought system of [[Kotodama]] (the spirit of words). Similar characteristics can be observed in "Yashikibome" songs performed in [[shishimai]] (lion dances) and [[fūryū odori]]. In contrast to Yoshuku Performing Arts, those with a stronger focus on disaster prevention are sometimes referred to as [[Josai Performing Arts]].

== Related Topics ==
* [[Yoshuku]]
* [[Kadotsuke]]

