These arts embody the act of preemptive celebration to pray for the realization of blessings, rooted in the belief and thought process associated with {{ill|Kotodama|ja|言霊}}. Similar characteristics can be observed in the "Yashiki-bome" songs of {{ill|lion dances|ja|獅子舞}} or {{ill|furyu dances|ja|風流踊り}}. In contrast to Yoshuku Performing Arts, forms of art with a stronger focus on warding off disasters are sometimes referred to as {{ill|Josai Performing Arts|ja|除災芸能}}.

